                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/gulp/edit/master/knpu/javascript.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Now for the most thrilling part: JavaScript. Create a new <code>js</code> directory
inside <code>app/Resources/assets</code> and a new file - let's call that <code>main.js</code>.</p>
<p>Ok, let's start with a jQuery document ready block and then log a movie quote
that combines two of my <em>favorite</em> things: UNIX and dinosaurs. Thank you
Michael Crichton. Let's add something visual to the bottom navbar too. A subtle
warning, if you will.</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="ded01e3389">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            
            5 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="app/Resources/assets/js/main.js">app/Resources/assets/js/main.js</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="1"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">$(<span class="hljs-built_in">document</span>).ready(<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span>(<span class="hljs-params"></span>) </span>{</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="2"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">    <span class="hljs-built_in">console</span>.log(<span class="hljs-string">'It\'s a Unix system, I know this'</span>);</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="3"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">    $(<span class="hljs-string">'.navbar-static-bottom'</span>).prepend(<span class="hljs-string">'&lt;span class="navbar-text"&gt;Life finds a way&lt;/span&gt;'</span>);</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="4"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">});</td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>With such a cool JavaScript file, I can't wait to include it on my site.
But, I can't just go add a <code>script</code> tag - <code>main.js</code> isn't in a public directory.
Gulp, halp!</p>
<h2 id="scripts-task-in-gulp">scripts Task in Gulp <a class="headerlink" href="javascript#scripts-task-in-gulp" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Create a new task called <code>scripts</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="d8580c1ff5">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-60" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
