<p>Inside here, we're going to do almost the exact same stuff we do with our
CSS. So let's copy the inside of <code>addStyle</code> and paste it in our task. Now
we need to make a bunch of small adjustments.</p>
<p>First, get rid of a few things, like the <code>sass</code> filter and <code>minifyCss</code>. We
<em>will</em> minify in a second, but we need to use a different tool.</p>
<p>Second, in <code>src()</code>, start with <code>config.assetsDir</code> then <code>/js/main.js</code>. We
also need jQuery. That already lives inside the <code>bower_components</code> directory.
So above <code>main.js</code>, add <code>config.bowerDir</code> - that new config sure is coming
in handy - then <code>/jquery/dist/jquery.js</code>.</p>
<p>And to put the cherry on top, change the <code>dest()</code> to <code>web/js</code> and give <code>concat()</code>
a filename - how about <code>site.js</code>.</p>
