<h2 id="minify-with-gulp-uglify">Minify with gulp-uglify <a class="headerlink" href="javascript#minify-with-gulp-uglify" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>One last challenge: <code>site.js</code> is <em>not</em> minified yet. Dinosaurs hate whitespace,
so let's fix that. For our styles, we used that <code>minifyCss</code> plugin. For JS,
we'll use one called <code>gulp-uglify</code>. Grab its perfect install statement,
stop gulp, and get that downloading:</p>
<pre><code>npm install --save-dev gulp-uglify</code></pre>
<p>We don't need the <code>require</code> line though, because <code>gulp-plugins-require</code> takes
care of that for us. We can go straight to work. Copy the <code>minifyCss</code> line so
that we have the cool <code>--production</code> flag behavior. Paste it and change things
to say <code>plugins.uglify()</code>:</p>
